Then he made a peanut butter sandwich and ate lunch.
When he finished eating, Poulin went back downstairs and set fire to Rabotâ€™s body in a failed attempt to conceal his crimes.
In the afternoon, Robert Poulin took a shotgun to St. Pius X High School in Ottawa, Ontario, wounded four people, including the seriously injured Mark Hough.
â€œIt seemed to me like he wanted to hit the walls,â€ said Pierre Millette, a student in the class where Poulin started shooting reported the Ottawa Citizen on October 28, 1975.
â€œWith all those people there he certainly could have killed or injured a lot of us if heâ€™d wanted to. It just seemed like he wasnâ€™t interested in doing that.â€
â€œI saw the body in the hall, but I didnâ€™t think it was the person who was doing the shooting. I thought was someone else who had been shot,â€ Millette would later tell the Coronerâ€™s Inquest.
Student Mike Malone lurched for the door, opened it for a split second, then slammed it shut again.
After Poulin fired four shots into the classroom, he retreated to the hallway and, in one final act of cowardice, Robert Poulin used his last shell to shoot himself in the head.
