Deadly school shootings in Canada | 1975 â€“Â 2013
Despite Canadaâ€™s relatively strict gun controls, there are still occasional shootings at schools, universities and collegesÂ in theÂ country.
Friday afternoon, at leastÂ fourÂ people were killedÂ in a shooting that involved a schoolÂ in the small Saskatchewan community of La Loche. Two more people have been critically injured in the shooting.
Hereâ€™s a list of other deadlyÂ school shootings that have happened in Canada.
2013: LesÂ RacinesÂ de vie Montessori,Â Gatineau, Que.
On April 5, 2013,Â two men diedÂ during a shootingÂ at the schoolâ€™s daycare. The shooter wasÂ identified as Robert Charron. Thirty-eight-year-old Neil Galliou wasÂ killed before Charron tookÂ his own life. Charron told staff to take the 53 children to safety before he opened fire.
Michelle Shegelski, 26, was one of three guards shot dead at the University of Alberta by Travis Baumgartner in June 2012. (Courtesy John Ernst)
2012: University of Alberta, Edmonton
Travis Baumgartner shot four of his co-workers â€” three fatally â€” in a robbery on the university campus on June 15, 2012. After pleading guilty, he wasÂ sentenced in 2013 to 40 years in prisonwith no chance of parole.
2007: C.W. Jeffries, Toronto
Jordan Manners, 15, died after beingÂ shot at his north-end Toronto school,Â C.W. Jeffries. Manners was a Grade 9 student.
Grade 9 student Jordan Manners was shot and killed at his north-end Toronto school in 2007. (CBC)
Two men were charged with first-degree murder in the death. They were referred to only as C.D. and J. W. because they were 17 years old at the time Manners was slain. After two trials, the two men were ultimatelyÂ found not guilty.
2006: Dawson College, Montreal
One woman was killed after aÂ shooting rampage at the Montreal CEGEPÂ on Sept. 13, 2006. Another 19 people were injured â€” several seriously â€” in the shooting. The shooter, 25-year-old Kimveer Gill, shot himself after a shootout began with police at the college.
2004: Bramalea Secondary School, Brampton, Ont.
A 47-year-old teacher at the school,Â Aysegul Candir, wasÂ shot and killed by her husband, 62-year-old Erhun Candir , in the parking lot of the Brampton, Ont., school in 2004. No students were harmed and it was deemed a domestic dispute by police.
Candir was found guilty of first-degree murder and was sentenced to life in prison in 2007.
1999:Â W.R. Myers High School, Taber, Alta.
A 14-year-old boy opened fire inside the W.R. Myers High School in Taber, Alta., on April 28, 1999.
Jason Lang died after being shot at his school in Taber, Alta., in 1999.
TheÂ shooting left 17-year-old student Jason Lang deadÂ and another student was seriously injured. The shooter, who could not be identified because of his age, was sentenced to three years in secure custody, and another seven years of probation.
1992: Concordia University,Â Montreal
Prof.Â Valery Fabrikant fired on his colleagues on Aug. 24, 1992. He killed four people and wounded one more.
1989: Lâ€™Ecole Polytechnique, Montreal
FourteenÂ female students and a college employee were killed, and another 13 were injured In the worst school shooting in Canadaâ€™s history.
14
On Dec. 6, 1989, Marc Lepine, 25, walked into a classroom in the school with a gun and separated the men and the women, telling the men to leave. He opened fire in the classroom, and then wandered the hallways of the school, committing suicide shortly after his rampage.
A ceremony on Mount Royal marks the 25th anniversary of the Polytechnique massacre on Dec. 6, 2014 in Montreal. (Ryan Remiorz/CP)
1978: Sturgeon Creek School, Winnipeg
A 17-year-old student shot and killed a 16-year-old student at the Winnipeg high school on Oct. 19, 1978.
1975: Saint Pius X, Ottawa
An 18-year-old student, Robert Poulin, opened fire on his classmates on Oct. 27, 1975, killing two people and wounding four more before killing himself. He had also raped and killed a 17-year-old girl prior to the shooting.
1975: Brampton Centennial Secondary School, Ontario
A 16-year-old student, Michael Slobodian, killed two people and wounded 13 othersÂ before killing himself.
